<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920221-0026</DOCNO><DOCID>920221-0026.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- United Technologies Inc.:   Photonics Subsidiary Formed   After 10 Years of Research</HL><DATE>02/21/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   UTX</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>COMMUNICATIONS TECHNOLOGY (CMT)DIVERSIFIED TECHNOLOGY (DTC)</IN><RE>CONNECTICUT (CT)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   United Technologies Corp. said it formed a new subsidiary,United Technologies Photonics Inc.   The unit will design, build and sell integrated-opticcomponents, modules and subsystems for a broad range ofapplications. Photonics is the technology of manipulating andtransforming signals and data with light rather thanconventional electronics.</LP><TEXT>   The new unit capitalizes on more than 10 years of work inthe company's research center. The new unit, with more than30 employees, will be moved to Bloomfield, Conn. UnitedTechnologies, which is based in Hartford, Conn., didn'tdisclose sales of the operation.   Photonics has applications in fiber optics, includingoptical navigation systems, cable television signaldistribution, antenna interconnects, telecommunications andinstrumentation.   United Technologies provides a broad range ofhigh-technology products and support services to theaerospace, building systems and automotive industries.</TEXT></DOC>